"4:48:18" : {s: 4, a: 48, w: 18, r: "فري", t: "ٱفْتَرَىٰٓ", l: "ٱفْتَرَىٰ", lc: 50, tl: "if'tarā", lb: "উদ্ভাবন করা, আরোপ করা, বানিয়ে বলা",e: "he has fabricated", b: "মিথ্যা আরোপ করে", f: 14, rm: "to cut/split/cleave, slander, fabricate (a lie). In this root the letter ي is changed to ا when the verb is joined to the pronominal. fariya - to be astonished/amazed, blame, repair. farriyun - new, strange, wonderful, remarkable, unheard, unprecedent."},
"4:48:19" : {s: 4, a: 48, w: 19, r: "اثم", t: "إِثْمًا", l: "إِثْم", lc: 35, tl: "ith'man", lb: "পাপ, গুনাহ",e: "a sin", b: "অন্যায়ের", f: 7, rm: "to commit a crime/sin or lie. ithm - sin, crime, guilt, iniquity, lie, anything that hinders from good deeds, harmful, anything which renders a person deserving of punishment, anything that pricks the mind as something evil, unlawful. athaam - punishment of wickedness, the requital. aathim - evil doer, one who sins. athiim - wicked person. taathiim - accusation of crime."},
"4:48:20" : {s: 4, a: 48, w: 20, r: "عظم", t: "عَظِيمًا", l: "عَظِيم", lc: 120, tl: "ʿaẓīman", lb: "প্রচন্ড",e: "tremendous", b: "বহু", f: 22, rm: "great, important, big, regard, honour, mighty, glorious, a man of moment, All-mighty, All-glorious, grievous, bounty/abounding, magnify/increase. azzama - to make great."},
